title: Yellen’s Sway Over Rates Puts Her Atop Most Influential Ranking
text: From bloomberg.com On the bookshelf behind the sofa in Janet Yellens spacious office at 20th Street and Constitution Avenue in Washington sits a framed photograph her staff gave her when she was changing jobs five years ago. In it, shes posed next to a poster she kept on her wall when she was president of the Federal Reserve Bank of San Francisco. Its that poster, the now ubiquitous World War II slogan in plain type under a small British crown. Keep Calm and Carry Onof course thats Yellens motto.
